data.description: Every blue moon, (or should we say every total eclipse) the Real Estate Fairy comes along, and finds the perfect home to showcase and outshine the rest amongst the market. This time, a gorgeous and incredibly spacious cape cod nestled near the shoreline in Harrison Township has been chosen to take that place.  Introducing 26570 Hickler Lane, a picturesque gem that offers modern updates and an open floor concept. Three massive bedrooms, three full bathrooms, living areas opened up, and more storage space than you'll probably ever need. Who needs a basement when you have this much garage space!?  Inside you will discover spacious living areas, a gourmet kitchen, and a primary bedroom that is bigger than you could possibly need! But wait, there's a LOT more!   Outside, lush manicured lawns inside a tall fenced in backyard create a private oasis for relaxation. Oh, did you see the garage yet? Yeah, that attached garage can hold FOUR FULL SIZE TRUCKS, and still have some room for storage! You know how everyone you know gets a little squeamish when they hear the word 'crawlspace?' The crawlspace here is probably the nicest and cleanest one you will ever see! (sorry home inspectors!)   Alright, let's wrap this up.  Newer stainless steel appliances, new vinyl wood floors (the nice ones!) just installed 3/24. The backyard is huge. And there's a shed, even though there's already a ridiculous amount of storage space. This place is right between the Metro Park trail and the water, which means not only is a convenient location for limitless things to do, it's near 16 Mile and i94, so you can get around on your routes rather quickly. Boat Launch and access to Lake St. Clair right down the street, this is the perfect home for those seeking refined living. Kitchen is spacious, furnace is new, and I would keep going but I'm running out of space, unlike this place. Submit your offer while you still can!
